Context: The George Brown College offers a three-year (six-semester) Computer Programmer Analyst program. The first two years focus on software application development and testing, while the final year develops advanced technical abilities and communication skills. Students are involved in project-based and experiential learning. In the third year, students are introduced to AI and Machine-Learning strategies and development, as well as mobile application development using the latest mobile devices. The program requirements include a personal computer with specifications of at least 16 GB RAM, 256 GB SSD Hard Drive, Quad-core i7 2.4GHz processor, 2GB Video Ram (4GB recommended), and a Webcam. Graduates may find career opportunities in areas such as database administration, systems analysis and design, consulting, application design and development, web application design and development, data architect (AI/Machine Learning), full-stack developer, and mobile application developer. Opportunities for systems development exist for corporate clients and smaller contract companies. If you enrol in January, you must complete semester 2 in the summer, May to August, of the same year. The program is subject to ongoing improvements which may result in course changes made in consultation with the Program Advisory Committee.

Learning Outcomes: The graduate will be able to identify, analyze, design, develop, implement, verify and document requirements for a computing environment; diagnose, troubleshoot, document and monitor technical problems using appropriate methodologies and tools; analyze, design, implement and maintain secure computing environments; communicate and collaborate with team members and stakeholders; select and apply strategies for personal and professional development; apply project management principles and tools when responding to requirements and monitoring projects within a computing environment; adhere to ethical, social media, legal, regulatory and economic requirements and/or principles in developing and managing computing solutions and systems; investigate emerging trends to respond to technical challenges; gather, analyze and define software system specifications based on functional and non-functional requirements; design, develop, document, implement, maintain and test software systems using industry-standard methodologies and existing technologies/frameworks; select and apply object-oriented and other design concepts and principles, as well as business requirements, to the software development process; gather requirements and model, design, implement, optimize and maintain data storage solutions; integrate network communications into software solutions by adhering to protocol standards.

Tuition & Fees: Domestic Tuition for the first two semesters is $4,266.00. Additional costs are subject to change for programs starting in Fall 2023 and at later dates. Financial Assistance information is not mentioned in the text.

Context: The Computer Programmer Analyst program is offered through George Brown College's School of Computer Technology at the Casa Loma Campus located at 146 Kendal Avenue. Fees for this program are subject to change for programs starting in Fall 2023 and at later dates. This program is approved for OSAP funding for applicants who meet OSAP eligibility criteria. Applicants must have an Ontario Secondary School Diploma or equivalent, grade 12 English (C or U), and grade 11 math (M or U) or grade 12 (C or U). Mature students may apply and take the Admissions Assessment for English and math, or consider upgrading to achieve the required credits. Students can visit georgebrown.ca/transferguide for information on course exemptions. Domestic students should apply through Ontario Colleges. The School of Computer Technology can be contacted at 416-415-5000, ext. 4287 or email computertechnology@georgebrown.ca, with office hours Monday – Thursday: 8 a.m. – 7 p.m., and Friday: 8 a.m. – 4 p.m. The Program Co-ordinator is Maziar Masoudi, who can be reached at 416-415-5000, ext. 3345 or email mmasoudi@georgebrown.ca. For more information about George Brown College and campus visits, call the Contact Centre at 416-415-2000 (TTY 1-877-515-5559) or long distance 1-800-265-2002. The Computer Programmer Analyst program information sessions and campus tours can be signed up for on the website.
